Package: murphyos-core
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3 (>= 3.11),
         python3-aiohttp,
         systemd,
         dbus,
         polkitd | policykit-1,
         curl
Recommends: murphyos-kmod-dkms,
            python3-fusepy,
            nftables
Suggests: murphyos-desktop,
          liboqs0,
          python3-oqs
Description: MurphyOS — AI-native Linux runtime with PQC security
 Core runtime for MurphyOS: Murphy System service, CLI tool, D-Bus bridge,
 FUSE filesystem, udev rules, PAM module, Polkit policies, nftables rules,
 DNS resolver, and post-quantum cryptography (PQC) key management.
 .
 Murphy is a universal AI automation system with HITL governance, swarm
 orchestration, and confidence-driven safety gates — integrated as native
 OS primitives.

Package: murphyos-desktop
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         murphyos-core,
         gnome-shell (>= 45)
Description: MurphyOS GNOME desktop integration
 GNOME Shell extension with confidence indicator, HITL approval
 notifications, Forge launcher, and PQC status display.  Includes
 Nautilus file-manager plugin for right-click Murphy processing.

Package: murphyos-kmod-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         dkms,
         linux-headers-generic | linux-headers-amd64 | linux-headers-arm64
Description: MurphyOS kernel module (DKMS)
 Loadable kernel module providing /dev/murphy-event (event bus),
 /dev/murphy-confidence (MFGC score), /sys/murphy/gates/ (governance),
 netfilter hooks (packet classification), and PQC HMAC-SHA3 event
 authentication.

Package: murphyos-edge
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         python3 (>= 3.11),
         systemd,
         curl
Description: MurphyOS edge/IoT minimal runtime
 Minimal Murphy runtime for Raspberry Pi, Jetson, and industrial edge
 devices.  Includes Sensor, Actuator, Command, and Agent engines with
 PQC security and GPIO integration.
